{
  "doc_id": "41207",
  "text": "The sarcomatoid variant of renal cell carcinoma (RCC) features a spindle-cell phenotype and has been reported to have a poor prognosis compared with other histological types of RCC [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . Some reports have noted that the prognosis of patients with sarcomatoid RCC (SRCC) is poor even after tyrosine kinase inhibitor treatment [CITATION_4] . However, we report our experience with a case of metastatic sarcomatoid RCC (mSRCC) in which the patient achieved long-term survival following multidisciplinary treatment. We also discuss the relevant literature.",
